The paper discusses the performance evaluation of urban autonomous vehicles, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses learning models from data, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The experiments performed on naturalistic driving data involve computer vision (cs.CV) and control systems (cs.SY).
